The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Friday, September 12, 2003 				 Dry flowers from Doon Express bomb bag
 Burdwan, Sept. 11: The  station authorities here received an alert from Howrah around  10.30 last night. It said there was a bomb in the Doon Express  about to enter platform.																								Police swung into action. Platforms were evacuated and passengers were asked to vacate the express as it screeched to halt. Coaches combed and luggage checked, a policeman noticed a cloth bag on the roof of the S-4 coach. He raised an alarm and the bag was brought down. It was stuffed with dry flowers and sticks. The police saw the hand of a prankster and the train left past midnight.
